                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.3715/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-11T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 11, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>343. Your 668, June 10, 4 p.m. Inform Cuban Embassy that in view of the
                    uncertainty of the situation resulting from recent incidents<note n="72"
                        xml:id="d471fn72">See <ref target="#pg_307">pp. 307</ref>–<ref
                            target="#pg_340">340</ref>.</note> we regret that we cannot authorize
                    any of our naval vessels to visit Spanish ports until we can feel reasonably
                    assured that such a visit could be made without undue risk. It is possible
                    therefore that it may be some weeks before we are in a position to comply with
                    the Embassy’s request.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
